            "text": "JSON Schema for Tools"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every tool you expose to Claude must have a JSON Schema definition. The schema tells the model what the tool is called, what it does, and what arguments to generate when invoking it. Claude reads these schemas at inference time and uses them to produce valid, structured "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "tool_use"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " blocks."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "JSON Schema tool definition structure diagram"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The schema is not just validation \u2014 it is the model's primary source of information about what a tool does and when to use it. A well-written description causes the right tool to be called at the right time. A vague description causes misuse or omission."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
